Title: 10 Hours ASMR Cooking Thailand's Food in the Rain | Relaxing NO MUSIC NO TALKING
Description:
Immerse yourself in the soothing sounds of rain and the aromatic allure of Thai cuisine with our 10-hour ASMR cooking experience. As the gentle rhythm of the rain sets a calming backdrop, witness the artful preparation of Thailand's most beloved dishes. From the sizzle of fresh ingredients hitting the hot pan to the gentle chop of herbs, every sound contributes to a symphony of relaxation and culinary delight. Discover the secrets of Thai spices and flavors as each dish comes together, offering a visual and auditory feast. Perfect for unwinding, studying, or simply enjoying a moment of peace, this video will transport you to a serene, rain-kissed world where the vibrant essence of Thailand's food culture comes to life. No talking, just the pure, natural sounds of cooking and rain - an escape to tranquility.

Title: 1 Hour of Heavenly Harp Music I Sarah Bhalla
Description:
I had been actively watching the weather, hoping the rain would hold off just long enough before the approaching storm rolled in from across the ocean. As I made my way to the cliffs, I passed through golden fields of mustard flowers, where a lone crane stood gracefully in the distance. The air was still, the calm before the storm. This was a beautiful session, and I hope you can feel the deep peace woven into these moments.

Just as I packed up my harp and started walking back, the first raindrops fell, a soft, gentle prelude to what was coming. By the time I reached the car and loaded everything, the rain had just begun a gentle shower, sweeping across the landscape I had just left behind. I sat for a moment, letting gratitude to God settle over me, a quiet acknowledgment that everything had unfolded at the perfect time.

All of the music is improvised around a few compositional ideas, played intuitively, flowing with the rhythm of this magnificent space.

Love to you,

Sarah

What is ASMR??
ASMR stands for Autonomous sensory meridian response (ASMR). 
It is a feeling of well-being combined with a tingling sensation in the scalp and down the back of the neck, as experienced by some people in response to a specific gentle stimulus, often a particular sound.

PLEASE NOTE: Even though ASMR can help you relax, it is in NO WAY a substitute for medical/psychological counsel, please reach out to your doctor if you're in need of medical support.

Plucking remains my favorite visual trigger, the first to put me to sleep because it's the derivation of the hand movements I love so much.

What is ASMR??
ASMR stands for Autonomous sensory meridian response (ASMR). 
It is a feeling of well-being combined with a tingling sensation in the scalp and down the back of the neck, as experienced by some people in response to a specific gentle stimulus, often a particular sound.

PLEASE NOTE: Even though ASMR can help you relax, it is in NO WAY a substitute for medical/psychological counsel, please reach out to your doctor if you're in need of medical support.

Autonomous sensory meridian response, sometimes auto sensory meridian response, is a tingling sensation that typically begins on the scalp and moves down the back of the neck and upper spine. Title: Healing Frequency Meditation (1111 Hz) | 1 hour handpan music | Malte Marten & Lynxk
Description:
I am so proud and happy to share this jam with you. Lynxk and I met a couple of weeks ago, when she had just started her handpan journey. In the meantime we did some handpan lessons and started playing gentle jams together. Her talent and openness is amazing and from a teachers perspective it just makes my heart smile to see her progress. Weâ€™ve been focusing on the very basics of handpan playing - the foundation of every jam: the chord progression. Goal of the first learning cycle is to deepen the understanding of the continuous change of chords. Next on is to implement new patterns, first percussive elements and little fill-ins to make one and the same pattern sound unique.
On a personal note it is deeply fulfilling to jam with her. The energy shifts as soon as we take the instruments on our labs and start to play. Sending love always â™¾ï¸ğŸ¤

Title: Taking Care of You When Youâ€™re Sick ğŸ¤’ SCI-FI SOLARPUNK ASMR â˜€ï¸ [Unusual Remedies, Deep Resonance]
Description:
NO MUSIC VERSION: https://youtu.be/7eqNJ06sfLY

You find yourself battling a mysterious illness, one that manifests in an array of strange symptomsâ€”like chromatic sweats, haptic hallucinations, and polarized vision. The city hospital dismissed your case as spring allergiesâ€¦But I know itâ€™s something more serious than that. After exhaustive research and numerous tests, I've begun to suspect that your condition might be a rare sensitivity to the recent solar flares. Here, in the quietness of my eco-friendly sanctuary, I will care for you. Using my scientific expertise, I am committed to unraveling the mystery of your illness and developing effective remedies. You are the most important person in my life, and I will keep you closeâ€”watching over you with unwavering vigilanceâ€”until we uncover the truth behind these unusual symptoms. 

When most people think of the futuristic genre, the word â€œcyberpunkâ€ comes to mind. However, there are many different categories that are similar (dread punk, bio punk, diesel punk). The "punk" genres in fiction encompass a variety of settings that mix technology, society, and often politics, each with its own distinctive look and philosophy. For this video, I wanted to focus on â€œsolar punkâ€ which is a genre that envisions a future shaped by sustainability, renewable energy, and a harmonious integration of human society with the natural world. My interpretation of it is that itâ€™s like a future way of life where solar energy is used to power everything, and everyone has a rooftop garden. I initially had the idea of harvesting solar energy through a wand-like device and using it to cure an illness. From that initial idea, I crafted the rest of the story based on that. My way of incorporating the sustainability aspect of this genre was to have this character collect a bunch of vintage objects. I hope you enjoy the ambience section at the end! I love when there's at least 10 minutes of nothing important happening in ASMR videos so I can actually fall asleep. Scratchy pencil sounds are one of my favorites :)

Title: 9-Hour Draw With Me âœ¿ Full Webtoon comic page drawing process + Pomodoro Timer 50/10 (Soft Music)
Description:
âœ¿ Ê•â€¢Ìá´¥â€¢Ì€Ê”ã£  Hi everyone! 

Happy Monday! I hope you all had a restful weekend and are having a great start to your week.

Today I am sharing something a bit... dare I say... crazy (Â´âŠ™Ï‰âŠ™`)! In an effort to kick my butt out of procrastination-mode and motivate myself to get working on my webcomic, I challenged myself to document my *entire* comic-making process â€” starting from a completely blank canvas to a fully lined and colored comic page from my Webtoon (that is still yet to be released), "Heart on a Stale Canvas" (â—â€¢á´—â€¢â—)â¤

The format of this video was inspired by the many "study with me" videos I used to play in the background while studying when I was still in University. I really wanted this video to be like a friend to help motivate you and draw with the entire dayãƒ½(ã€ƒï¼¾â–½ï¼¾ã€ƒ)ï¾‰ 

I included a Pomodoro timer to help break up focus time and break time into 50-minute and 10-minute sessions respectively. The 10-minute break sessions are little chitty-chattys with me explaining a bit about my process and what I accomplished in the preceding focus sessions. I also included a 40-minute lunch break where I film myself preparing and eating some yummy onigiri (rice balls) (à·†Ë™áµ•Ë™à·†)â™¡

There were many ups and downs throughout the filming process (Namely, running into technical difficulties à²¥_à²¥) but I managed to push through nonetheless! I really hope you all enjoy and learn something new about the comic-making process (ï¼¾â–½ï¼¾)

Thank you all so much for watching! 
â¤  Riniapple

***Video Editing Note***
I apologize for the audio cutting out a bit periodically during the first break. I'm pretty sure this audio issue is fixed for the rest of the video!

Title: Harp in a Giant Redwood Tree: 1 Hour Healing Music | Sarah Bhalla
Description:
There is no feeling like being in the forest among the giant ancient redwood trees. The air shifts, like youâ€™ve stepped into a world outside of time. Coast redwoods (Sequoia sempervirens) are the tallest beings on Earth and some of the oldest, living over 2,000 years. 

This beautiful tree endured a severe fire that hollowed out the inside. Redwood bark is incredibly fire-resistant; if enough of the tissue remains, the tree will heal and thrive.  This incredible living being draws many visitors each year, and I felt so humbled to be here, to meet both locals and travelers who love this forest. Many come here routinely to walk among the trees, to feel a connection, and to find healing. 

A few wonderful animals call the forest home, and some even sang along once the music started. Listen closely and youâ€™ll hear owls and the playful Stellerâ€™s Jay. To sit within this towering Redwood and feel the harpâ€™s sound vibrate through the tree, itâ€™s hard to put that into words.  There was a deep presence in those moments, shared with the many beautiful souls I met here. This lives close to my heart, and Iâ€™m grateful to share these moments.

All of the music is improvised and includes a melody that came to me as a child. This chord structure is one I always return to, one of the first I ever improvised to, and it always feels like coming home.

So much love to you,

Sarah

Title: Forest Meditation: 1 Hour Harp Music | Sarah Bhalla
Description:
Wishing you a very happy New Year, full of peace. Iâ€™ve been reflecting lately with so much gratitude in my heart. So thankful to God for everything.

I returned to one of my favorite forests over two winter afternoons to record this forest meditation. The light fades so quickly this time of year, so I went back again to catch those last soft rays of afternoon sun. This piece is a prayer from the heart, improvised around a few musical ideas, recorded live alongside the sounds of nature.

Iâ€™ve also been trying a new camera lens that brings the small details a little closer. The harp is such a special instrument, you can see the strings moving and vibrating with the music. I would love to hear what you think of the new lens and how it feels to you.

As we step into this new year together, I hope you feel encouraged, held, and surrounded by kindness. Iâ€™ve been reflecting on how much it matters to choose grace, toward others and toward ourselves, to keep choosing love.

Wishing you a year filled with peace, joy, and so much love. Thank you, truly, for being here.
